Thank you in advance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/umance.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/14/02 3:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 axe spec vs trows (Dane)</span><hr size=1> I haven't noticed any big change rvr with new patch, I could never reliably solo tanks before the patch.<br>
<br>
Your main prey remains the same, casters/healers and rogues some times.  Friars are a pain as well as wardens, but can be done.<br>
<br>
Your snare/mez and sprint serve you far better than hoping for a parry.  Also in the swirling rvr fights, the last place a skald wants to be is toe to toe with a tank class.  You should knife fight and skirmish.<br>
<br>
RA's I think for this type of skald should be:<br>
<br>
Aug dex 2, mastery of pain 3, purge, first aid 2, ignore pain.  I would suggest purge/fa2/IP  in that order then mop3. <p><center>
